---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Documentation - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-neutral-50 p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-neutral-900 mb-4">
          Documentation
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600">
          Everything you need to know about Helpmaton
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Getting Started
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            New to Helpmaton? Start here! We'll guide you through creating your
            first workspace, setting up agents, and uploading documents.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/getting-started"
            class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
          >
            Read Getting Started Guide →
          </a>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Working with Agents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Learn how to create, configure, and manage your AI agents. From
            basic setup to advanced configurations, we've got you covered.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating your first agent</li>
            <li>Configuring agent personalities</li>
            <li>Setting up agent workflows</li>
            <li>Managing multiple agents</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Agent Memory System
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Agents remember important facts, people, and events from
            conversations through a sophisticated stratified memory
            architecture. This enables context-aware responses informed by past
            interactions.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Stratified memory architecture with temporal grains</li>
            <li>
              Progressive summarization (daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly,
              yearly)
            </li>
            <li>Semantic vector search for memory retrieval</li>
            <li>
              Plan-based memory retention (Free: 48h working + 30d summaries,
              Pro: 240h + 120d)
            </li>
            <li>Automatic memory cleanup and management</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Workspaces
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Organize your AI agents into workspaces. Each workspace is like a
            separate container with its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <div
            class="mb-4 p-4 bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Workspace credits are used for AI provider calls
              (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.), not for platform subscription costs. You
              can either provide your own API keys or purchase credits through Helpmaton.
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating and managing workspaces</li>
            <li>Setting spending limits (for AI provider costs)</li>
            <li>Adding API keys (BYOK) or purchasing credits</li>
            <li>
              Team collaboration and subscription sharing (Pro plans support
              unlimited managers)
            </li>
            <li>Workspace permissions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Documents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Upload and organize documents to give your agents knowledge. Learn
            about supported formats, organization, and best practices.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Uploading documents</li>
            <li>Organizing with folders</li>
            <li>Supported file formats</li>
            <li>Document management tips</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Usage Analytics & Monitoring
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Comprehensive token usage tracking and monitoring tools to help you
            understand and optimize your AI spending. View detailed analytics
            across all dimensions of your usage.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>
              Token usage tracking (prompt, completion, reasoning, cached
              tokens)
            </li>
            <li>Daily and hourly aggregation</li>
            <li>Historical data with date range filtering</li>
            <li>Per-workspace and per-agent breakdowns</li>
            <li>Cost tracking and budget monitoring</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Webhooks & Integrations
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Connect Helpmaton to your existing tools and workflows. Set up
            webhooks, integrate with APIs, and automate your processes.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Setting up webhooks</li>
            <li>Real-time streaming with Server-Sent Events (SSE)</li>
            <li>Webhook events and payloads</li>
            <li>Integration examples</li>
            <li>Troubleshooting webhooks</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            MCP Servers
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Extend your agents' capabilities with Model Context Protocol (MCP)
            servers. Connect to external APIs, databases, and custom tools to
            enable powerful integrations.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>What are MCP servers?</li>
            <li>Configuring MCP servers</li>
            <li>Enabling MCP servers for agents</li>
            <li>Authentication and security</li>
            <li>Use cases and examples</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Billing & Pricing
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Understanding Helpmaton's pricing structure and how costs work.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
                What's Included in Your Subscription
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Your monthly subscription covers all Helpmaton platform
                services:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Hosting and infrastructure</li>
                <li>Agent configuration and management</li>
                <li>Agent memory system and analytics</li>
                <li>Workspaces and team collaboration</li>
                <li>Document storage and search</li>
                <li>All Helpmaton-related API calls</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
                AI Provider Calls (Separate)
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                AI provider calls (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc.) are <strong
                  >not included</strong
                > in your subscription. You have two flexible options:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>BYOK (Bring Your Own Key):</strong> Use your own LLM API
                  keys and pay providers directly while enjoying all Helpmaton features
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Purchase credits:</strong> Buy credits through Helpmaton
                  for usage-based billing with transparent pricing
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
                Cost Control & Spending Limits
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Set granular spending limits to maintain budget control:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Daily, monthly, or yearly spending limits</li>
                <li>Limits at both workspace and individual agent levels</li>
                <li>Automatic credit reservation with atomic operations</li>
                <li>
                  Advanced pricing support (tiered rates, reasoning tokens,
                  cached tokens)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-3">
              This separation keeps your platform costs predictable while giving
              you complete flexibility in how you handle AI provider costs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            API Reference
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            For developers who want to integrate Helpmaton programmatically.
            Full REST API documentation with examples and code snippets.
          </p>
          <div
            class="mb-4 p-4 bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
              Flexible Authentication
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
              Multiple authentication methods to fit your workflow:
              session-based authentication for web users, JWT tokens (24-hour
              expiration) for API access, workspace API keys for programmatic
              integration, and OAuth support.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="https://app.helpmaton.com/docs/api"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
          >
            View API Reference →
          </a>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
            Self-Hosting
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Helpmaton is open source! The source code is available on GitHub, so
            you can spin up your own instance, customize it to your needs, and
            run it on your own infrastructure. Full control, zero vendor
            lock-in.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4 mb-4"
          >
            <li>Complete source code available</li>
            <li>Setup instructions included</li>
            <li>Customize to your needs</li>
            <li>Run on your own infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/djinilabs/helpmaton"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
          >
            View on GitHub →
          </a>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-gradient-primary rounded-lg shadow-colored p-6 text-white"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Need Help?</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-white/90">
            Can't find what you're looking for? Our support team is here to
            help!
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="inline-block bg-white text-primary-600 px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
            >
              Contact Us
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://discord.gg/Zf9Q7GpuKx"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-transparent text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Join Discord
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
